inspect:
Since the router holds references to many parts of the system
like engines, controllers and the application itself, inspecting
the route set can actually be really slow, therefore we default
alias inspect to to_s.
NamedRouteCollection:
A NamedRouteCollection instance is a collection of named routes, and also
maintains an anonymous module that can be used to install helpers for the
named routes.
formatter: Returns the value of attribute formatter
set: Returns the value of attribute set
named_routes: Returns the value of attribute named_routes
default_scope: Returns the value of attribute default_scope
router: Returns the value of attribute router
disable_clear_and_finalize: Returns the value of attribute disable_clear_and_finalize
resources_path_names: Returns the value of attribute resources_path_names
default_url_options: Returns the value of attribute default_url_options
request_class: Returns the value of attribute request_class
routes: Returns the value of attribute set
mounted_helpers:
Contains all the mounted helpers across different
engines and the `main_app` helper for the application.
You can include this in your classes if you want to
access routes for other engines.
extra_keys:
Generate the path indicated by the arguments, and return an array of
the keys that were not used to generate it.
url_for: The +options+ argument must be +nil+ or a hash whose keys are *symbols*.
